 Conservatives fear successful public plan undermines their arguments Paul Waldman. "The Public Option and the Hope of Health Care Reform". American Prospect. December 23, 2008: "Republicans fear that the public option would work, and therefore undermine their broader arguments about the evil of government and the perfection of the market (and make voters thankful to Democrats to boot)."
